From: topemalheiro <topemalheiro@hotmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 05:17:51 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Fix all-day event date corruption for EAS 16.1 (Oct-Dec)

The local pad() helper in getIsoUtcString() returned a raw Number for
values >= 10. When building the fake-UTC date-only string used for
EAS 16.1 all-day events, the first concatenation was:

  UTC.year (Number) + pad(UTC.month + 1) (Number for Oct-Dec)

which performed arithmetic instead of string concatenation, yielding
malformed dates like 203607T000000Z for 2026-10-07.

Always returning a String from pad() forces concatenation for all
month/day/hour/minute/second values.
---
 content/includes/tools.js | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/content/includes/tools.js b/content/includes/tools.js
index 122606f..8da8e8f 100644
--- a/content/includes/tools.js
+++ b/content/includes/tools.js
@@ -285,7 +285,7 @@ var tools = {
             if (number < 10) {
                 return '0' + number;
             }
-            return number;
+            return number.toString();
         }
         
         if (onlyDate && fakeUTC) {
-- 
